org.spongepowered.api.profile

Interface GameProfileManager


  • public interface GameProfileManager
    Manages GameProfile creation and data population.

    The manager may cache the data of a request for faster lookups. Note that the cached data may not always be up to date.

      • get

        default CompletableFuture<GameProfile> get(UUID uniqueId)
        Looks up a GameProfile by its unique ID.

        This method checks the local profile cache before contacting the profile servers. Use get(UUID, boolean) to disable the cache lookup.

        The returned CompletableFuture throws an ExecutionException caused by a ProfileNotFoundException if the profile does not exist or an IOException if a network error occurred.

        Parameters:
        uniqueId - The unique ID
        Returns:
        The result of the request
